parameters:
\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>This is it... without a
doubt, magic is being emitted from this device...!

\OC[5] Kuhahaha! Falling into my trap twice!! The
holy knight isn't that impressive after all!

\CE[94]\OC[5]\n<???>Nice to meet you, Sir Holy
Knight Rain. I am one of the executives of the
Demon Alliance Army, a demon named Dimon.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>The Demon Alliance Army...!? And
why do you know my name...?

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Your nickname is well-known
even in the demon world, \ANN[1]. It's quite
impressive for someone so young.

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>However, I never expected to
catch such a big fish... It seems luck is on my
side. Kufufu...

\OC[31]\N<Rain>What does this mean...! And why are
demons here...!?

\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Hehe... Well, since you've come
this far as promised, and more importantly, I'm in
a good mood. I'll answer your question.

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Of course, the fact that I,
a demon, am here in a place that is the complete
opposite of the human world, is all part of our
strategy to dominate the human realm.

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>This place is the complete
opposite of the battlefield... and also the
backside of the royal capital.

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>In other words, if we can
attack from this side, we can launch a pincer
attack. If that happens, it's only a matter of
time before we dominate the human realm.

\CE[77]\OC[31]\N<Rain>That's ridiculous... I don't
know how strong you are, but humans are not weak
enough to be easily defeated by one person!

\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Yes, of course I don't intend to do
that. I plan to prepare enough forces to stab the
army in the back firmly.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>That's impossible. Even if this
place is far from the military's line of sight,
there's no way they could bring in a demon army of
that scale from such a distant location in the
demon world!

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Well, I suppose that's true.
If we were to summon the demon clan, it would
indeed be like that.

\CE[77]\OC[31]\N<Rain>No way, the person who
attacked on the first floor... was being
controlled by you...!?

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>This device is a device that
continues to emit a certain magic.

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>The magic I developed that
amplifies desires... its name is
\{\C[17]'Nightmare Heaven'\C[0]\}.

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Desire is the source of
energy for humans, who are the most greedy
creatures with longing hearts. It can be said that
it drives their actions. 'Nightmare Heaven'
stimulates and amplifies those desires.

\OC[5]\N<Dimon>As you have experienced, those who
let their desires surpass reason become like
animals. Once they reach that state, it becomes
very easy to control them.

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>In other words, controlling
desires is synonymous with controlling humans.

\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Acting according to one's desires
may actually be the true form that humans
inherently desire. However, for humans who have
acquired reason, it may appear as a nightmare-like
state, don't you think?

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Therefore, 'Nightmare
Heaven'! Don't you think it's a good name with
quite a biting irony?

\CE[77]\OC[31]\N<Rain>This is beyond perverse! Are
you planning to control all the people of Hakudeti
with that magic?!

\CE[77]\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Yes, that's right. It
was quite a challenge, you know~ I carefully
operated the device for a whole year while hiding
myself so as not to be discovered.

\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Once the magic has spread to a
certain extent, if I 'ignite' it, the recipient
will become a beast like that man who attacked
you. After that, all I have to do is guide them
appropriately and they will become powerful
soldiers.

\CE[77]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I won't let you do such a
thing!! And are you really happy to win by
involving innocent civilians and resorting to such
dirty methods!?

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Oh, how sweet~!! This is a
battle between races, you know? Whether they're
babies or ordinary citizens, we'll use everything
available to secure victory, of course!

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>It's quite impressive that
you can still speak with such a mouth in that
state.

\OC[5]\N<Dimon>By the way, we've set it up so that
pressure is applied on the front lines to prevent
them from diverting forces to our side. So even if
you manage to escape this predicament, don't
expect any reinforcements.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>Could it be because of the sudden
intense monster attacks on the capital city
recently...!

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Yes, that's right. It's
going exactly as planned. You're already done for.

\OC[5]\N<Dimon>It was within my expectations that
forces would be diverted from the capital city to
Hakudeti. Even though it was done slowly,
continuously casting 'Nightmare Heaven' on a town
of this size, there's no way the abnormality would
go unnoticed.

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>So, that's why I set up this
trap... but to catch not just any ordinary knight,
but a holy knight! Do you understand the joy of
how well this plan has worked??

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Well, it's about time for
you to become my pawn. Since I've captured such a
big fish, I'll make sure to recover the costs
properly.

\OC[5]\N<Dimon>It seems like you're resisting the
effects of 'Nightmare Heaven' with your strong
magical power and resilient mental strength, but
this time, I'll make sure to thoroughly corrupt
you.

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Hehehe, shall we leave it to
those kids then?

\CE[94]\OC[5]\N<Dimon>Well then, I'm busy so let's
end it here. Oh, indulging in desires is such a
pleasant thing. Please enjoy yourself.

\CE[77]\C[13]\OC[31]\N<Inner Rain>(These
tentacles... they're strong, but strangely gentle
in certain places...)

\OC[31]\C[13]\N<Inner Rain>(No...! This body
belongs only to Jazz...! I don't want to... but it
feels so good...)

The tentacles responded to Rain's desires,
destroying her equipment and tightly entwining
around her body.

\OC[31]\N<Rain>Haa, haa... \. This is bad, if I
continue like this... it's playing right into that
demon's hands!

\OC[31]\C[13]\N<Inner Rain>(This... this isn't the
time to be losing to such magic!)

\OC[31]\C[13]\N<Inner Rain>(Calm down... With my
power, I can easily break free from this kind of
restraint...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I can't believe the Demon
Alliance Army is involved...

\OC[31]\N<Rain>Anyway... I have to destroy this
device...!

\OC[31]\N<Rain>If I examine these fragments of the
device, I might be able to understand something. I
should keep them...

\CE[79]\OC[31]\N<Rain>I need to hurry... I have to
go back...!

Will you fight against the resurrected dungeon
boss? *After defeating it, it will revive again
after one day.
